I stand before you today to take full responsibility for my actions. I am pleading guilty to the offense of speeding, as I understand the severity of my actions and the danger I posed to others on the road.

On the day of the incident, I made a regrettable decision to test the speed capabilities of my new car. I was overwhelmed by the excitement and thrill, which clouded my judgment. However, I am fully aware that this does not excuse my behavior.

I must acknowledge that this is not the first time I have been involved in speeding incidents. I have received penalty points for three previous offenses on my license. I deeply regret these past transgressions and understand the need for consequences.

Furthermore, I would like to bring the court's attention to the fact that I have no other criminal record. This incident stands as an isolated action, which I deeply regret. I assure the court that I have learned from my past mistakes and will strive to make better choices in the future.

I would also like to mention that I have been diagnosed with ADHD. While this does not excuse my behavior, it may shed light on my impulsiveness and difficulty with making rational decisions in the heat of the moment. I am seeking treatment and support to manage my condition effectively.

I want to express my genuine remorse for the potential harm I caused to those around me. The safety of others should always be a priority, and I deeply regret any fear or anxiety I may have caused. I understand the gravity of my actions and assure the court that I am committed to changing my behavior.

In conclusion, I humbly request the court's leniency and understanding as I take full responsibility for my actions. I acknowledge the need for consequences and assure the court that I am committed to personal growth and making amends. Thank you for your time and consideration.

